ABOUT
The owners of the fine-dining spot Marker 32, Ben and Liza, opened the Palm Valley Fish Camp near Ponte Vedra Beach in 2009. Located on the Intracoastal, Palm Valley Fish Camp is the result of the Groshell’s vision to create a restaurant with a neighborhood feel, the freshest seafood, amazing views, and old favorite entrees with creative, new twists.
This venue’s interior is as fresh and inviting as the catch of the day, and the light from the sun shimmers off the water as a simple gift just before the sun sets. The locals know exactly where to come to get that getaway feel right here at home.
If the freshest oysters on the half shell and true southern seafood awaken your taste buds, stop in today for an unforgettable lunch or dinner with lively atmosphere, knowledgeable and friendly service, and spectacular views.
